courses.learning_outcomes:
After completing this course, the students will be able to:   
1. understand what it takes to be a successful IT entrepreneur;   
2. be encouraged to be more market-oriented when developing IT products/services in their studies and workplaces;   
3. know how to apply major marketing concepts to the task of profitably winning business from targeted customers;   
4. gain hands-on experiences in identifying business opportunities and developing business and marketing plan through case studies and course projects.

At the end of the course of studies, students will have acquired the ability to  
1. Comprehend the mechanisms, applications, and limitations of techniques commonly used in training and inference of deep neural network algorithms;  
2. Utilize proper engineering techniques for deep neural network models;  
3. Formulate hypotheses and conduct experiments employing these techniques;  
4. Analyse experimental results obtained by these techniques and one’s own practices and derive the conclusions that are supported or not supported by one’s data;  
5. Propose new engineering approaches and techniques to further enhance deep neural network training and inference execution.

courses.course_syllabus:
At the end of the course of studies, students will have acquired  
1. knowledge in deep neural network (DNN) architecture and structures;  
2. knowledge in DNN training and inference procedures and algorithms;  
3. knowledge in efficient computing of DNN training and inference.

courses.learning_outcomes:
At the end of the course of studies, a student should be able to

1. Have a good understanding and appreciate the characteristics of a computer science related work environment, including employer expectation, management structure of a team, industrial standards and practices, trends and common issues in computer science, etc.;  
2. Carry out basic duties in a computer science related work environment;  
3. Exhibit good etiquette in the workplace;  
4. Work independently as well as in a team environment; and  
5. Communicate effectively and efficiently with peers, supervisors and possibly also clients.
